race.comment: VIERVILLE (3) returned from a six-month spell with a gutsy all-the-way win over 1200m at Scone, hanging on for dear life when pressured. Two failures from two second-up runs is the only query, but he should get his own way in front and prove tough to reel in again. SMART CRY (10) had her chance but was just even through the line when resuming over 1200m at this track last time. Scored second-up last prep. On trial at this distance but she is lightly raced and looks up to the task. ANTILOCAPRA (5) has finished midfield in two consecutive Class 3 Highways, the latest over 1500m at Rosehill. Back in trip with the blinkers going on. Hard to beat in this easier race. TICKLE ME PINK (7) returned in a much stronger race than this at Port Macquarie last start and was just fair. Can run a much better race today in this company. MYALABY (9) was back in form last time out at Taree and looks a sound each-way hope.
